    Title: I Ching
Title: The Army
---
Discipline in the army is achieved by the mature and experienced man who
gains the support of the ruler and arouses the spirit of the people. Passions
of combat, however, should not lead to cruelty and revenge. Firm-heartedness
and correctness should form the basis of action.
